acceptance_criteria: "Report high-signal source/test/docs surfaces, linked-item coverage gaps, command/runtime contract risks, and exact pm or repo commands used."
parent: pm-57vh
resolution: Source/test/docs coverage findings were mapped to concrete items; package namespace contracts and historical linked-file ownership remain tracked as open follow-ups while the aggregate status-all regression was fixed.
expected_result: Command-surface and artifact-ownership gaps are tracked individually without duplicates.
actual_result: pm-y1o4 remains open for package namespace contract lookup; pm-bhtx is closed; pm-j8z6 remains open for dedicated linked-file reconciliation. Current validate --check-files baseline warns with 146 missing linked paths and 162 orphaned paths after broad historical mutations were pruned.
comments[3]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-06-25T04:53:47.696Z",codex-pm-ecosystem-audit-20260625,"Sub-agent evidence: read AGENTS.md and inspected source/test/docs/contracts/release surfaces without code or tracker mutations. Inventory: src/cli/commands=75 files, src/core=121, src/sdk=14, src/mcp=2, packages=51, scripts=30, docs=33, workflows=6, tests=269. Existing historical coverage is mostly closed under pm-xau3/pm-w13j/pm-ud1x/pm-7v9s/pm-krwu/pm-f2ne/pm-6tch; live pm-xezi had no linked artifacts at inspection time. Open stories pm-5dbn/pm-b4cp/pm-srex are useful but sparse as current linked file maps. One concrete new candidate: package namespace contracts, because pm changelog --help works and changelog generate contracts work, but pm contracts --command changelog --flags-only --json returns unknown_command; no open direct duplicate found by status-all search. Verification run: pm health --check-only --summary --json ok; pnpm contracts:check current."
  "2026-06-25T05:16:05.394Z",codex-ecosystem-auditor,"Lane closure evidence: source/tests/docs/command-surface audit produced inventory and one concrete command-contract issue pm-y1o4. Aggregate status-all regression pm-bhtx was also fixed and closed from this lane evidence. File ownership reconciliation pm-j8z6 closed with validate --check-files ok."
  "2026-06-25T05:21:44.393Z",codex-ecosystem-auditor,"Correction after changelog review: pm-j8z6 was reopened because broad linked-file reconciliation touched hundreds of old PM records and was pruned from this product-fix PR. The lane's source/command inventory remains valid; linked-file hygiene is tracked separately as open backlog."
